snippet.title: Sunspot AR4371 ERUPTS! M-Class Flares Hit - Radio Blackouts Possible in USA, Europe, Asia TODAY
snippet.description:
🚨 AR4371 FIRES M-CLASS FLARES - RADIO BLACKOUTS HIT USA, EUROPE & ASIA
It’s happening. AR4371 just escalated from C-class baseline activity to M-class flares, and radio blackouts are now striking across three continents. After days of monitoring this delta-bearing sunspot, it’s following the exact same progression that made AR4366 the most prolific flare producer of Solar Cycle 25.
WHAT’S HAPPENING NOW:
AR4371 fired multiple M-class flares overnight from prime Earth-facing position at center disk. NOAA forecasts 65% probability for continued M-class activity and 25% chance of X-class eruptions through February 10th. Every flare triggers R1 to R2 radio blackouts across whichever hemisphere faces the sun at the moment of eruption.
WHO’S AFFECTED:
🇺🇸 USA - High-frequency communications disrupted
🇪🇺 Europe - Aviation and maritime systems experiencing interference
🇯🇵 Asia - Emergency services coordination challenged
As Earth rotates through its 24-hour cycle, different regions move into the strike zone. Morning UTC hits Europe and Africa. Afternoon UTC impacts Asia and Australia. Evening UTC affects North and South America.
WHY THIS MATTERS:
AR4371 gained delta magnetic configuration - the same dangerous structure that powered AR4366 to produce ten X-class flares in nine days. Delta configuration means opposite magnetic polarities within the same penumbra, creating extreme stress in the solar magnetic field. When those field lines snap through magnetic reconnection, they unleash explosive energy.
We’re watching the escalation phase right now. C-class baseline jumped to M-class territory. If AR4371 continues following AR4366’s pattern, X-class eruptions could be next.
INFRASTRUCTURE AT RISK:
✈️ Aviation using HF radio for transoceanic communication
🚢 Maritime operations relying on shortwave ship-to-shore contact
📡 Amateur radio operators across all bands
🚨 Emergency services using HF for disaster coordination
M-class flares ionize Earth’s D-layer ionosphere, absorbing high-frequency radio signals that normally bounce off the atmosphere and travel thousands of miles. The result: dead air, signal loss, communication blackout.
THE FORECAST:
AR4371 remains in optimal Earth-facing geometry for the next 5-7 days. Every flare during this window hits Earth directly. NOAA space weather forecasters continue monitoring this fast-evolving region while AR4366 - though declining - still carries beta-gamma-delta complexity and remains capable of additional eruptions from the western limb.

5. Stock Market View: एक्सपर्ट्स के मुताबिक रिलायंस का शेयर ₹1,700 से ₹1,800 के लेवल कब छुएगा?

snippet.title: OFAC licenses 49, 50 for Venezuela . nvor 1245
snippet.description:
OFAC continues issuing licenses authorizing oil and gas production, exploration, and commercialization in Venezuela. In addition to several previous licenses issued during the last few weeks, OFAC has issued general license 49 which approves contingent negotiations, operations, tenders, bidding and other such activities necessary for inclusion of new business participants in the Venezuelan oil and gas industry accepting nationals or persons related to Russia, China, Iran, North Korea and Cuba. Payments must be channelized through foreign deposits sovereign funds. OFAC license 50 is an example of application of license 49 as it explicitly allows Chevron, Repsol, ENI, BP and Shell to increase their presence in Venezuela. Other companies that are in the process of securing participation in the Venezuelan petroleum business such as Maurel & Prom, whose executives recently met with honorable president Delcy Rodríguez are expected to be awarded fresh licenses as well.    #venezuela

snippet.title: Anti-Ice & HAM, ARRL Directory, GMRS For Emergencies, Hamvention 2026, FCC Enforcement Roundup
snippet.description:

02:52 "FCC Ham Radio, CB Radio & GMRS Enforcement Roundup"

The new updated 2026 ARRL Repeater Directory is now available and shipping.. on paper... in the form of a book. For only $22.95, OR $19.95 if you're an ARRL member, you too can have this massive, 1-pound pile of dead-tree shavings placed into a truck, shipped across the country and hand-delivered directly to your mailbox in only a matter of days. This new, updated ARRL Repeater Directory lists over 22,000 ham radio repeaters and now features a Quick Find Index to help you locate repeaters by city... Don't delay and Order yours now, because if you don't, you'll be have to resort to using the internet to look up everything much faster and easier.
A veritable sh!tstorm has been spewing across all social media amongst the licensed ham radio crowd after a single 20-second video was posted on TikTok by some unknown woman, suggesting that Anti-Ice protesters should consider using HAM radios for communication and coordination of their anti-ice protests, as an alternative to the Signal Chat app that they have been previously using. The anonymous woman, that based on her appearance and in the opinion of many, does not appear to be mentally stable and reportedly has zero influence or power in the anti-ice protesting community, has successfully caused the entire ham radio community to completely lose its collective mind, resulting in her video going viral, getting her message out to even more people and making her famous even though there have been zero reports of any anti-ice protesters actually taking her advice.
Residents in Corry, Pennsylvania are building a GMRS community radio network for emergency communications, independent of cell phone or internet infrastructure.  This fast growing GMRS Emergency Comms network is built on a weekly GMRS Radio Net to allow local residents to test their radios, share information and practice emergency communication skills. The thriving new GMRS community currently boasts 12 active members but they hope to double that number by the end of next year.
The theme for upcoming 2026 Hamvention has been chosen to be "Radio Adventure!"  Which according to the HamVention organizers is representative of the ham radio hobby, pointing out POTA, SOTA, Field Days and balloon launches of examples of just how adventurous the ham radio hobby is.
In this month's FCC Enforcement Roundup, here is the breakdown of what the FCC accomplished during the month of January 2026:
The FCC Proposed 4 fines for violations of the radio Pirate Act, totaling $80,000 dollars.
The FCC sent a mean letter to the Vasquez Broadcasting corporation because of broadcast antenna structure violations
The FCC published a Consent Decree Order regarding the transfer of some commercial radio stations in Guam
They settled an ongoing investigation against a Telecom company 
The FCC submitted their Annual PIRATE radio Act report to congress,
And the part you've all been waiting for.  The grand total of mean letters, fines and jail time for CB radio, GMRS and ham radio operators violating FCC rules for the month of January 2026 was: ZERO.

• warum 15 m oft das zuverlässige DX-Band ist
• weshalb 10 m spektakulär – aber nicht immer offen – ist
